==English==


===Etymology===
'''foul or unpleasant'''
: [[skeevy]] (from Latin- ''schifo'' meaning disgusted or sickened) + [[rank]]
'''promiscuous woman'''
: [[scold]] + [[brank]] (Middle English- meaning frolicsome and often lascivious conduct)
'''dance'''
: Jamaican origin

===Noun===
'''skank'''
#Any [[substance]] considered particularly [[foul]] or [[unpleasant]]
#A [[promiscuous]] [[woman]]
#A [[dance]] performed to [[ska]].

